content:
Orchestrate every part of the service experience and provide meaningful, personalized interactions to your customers from a unified console. The Insurance Agent Console ties together powerful components that elevate the productivity of customer service representatives (CSRs) and present a 360-degree view of the customer.

Assign permission sets based on required access to Service Excellence for Insurance features.
Use Identity Verification to verify the identity of a customer or their authorized representative, protecting PII and complying with data regulations.

The Insurance Agent Console provides:
View a timeline of interactions
Get contextual alerts
Take relevant actions
Search knowledge articles

Customer service representatives can view an insurance customer's basic information on the Profile Card. Timeline provides a comprehensive view of customer-related activities.
Record Alerts help stay on top of changes related to customers, with snooze and dismiss options.

Show consolidated views of policies and claims details in the Insurance Agent Console for quick assistance.
Configure actions using flows or quick actions, and use Action Launcher to quickly run service actions.
Know the current sentiment of customers based on past engagements.
title: Insurance Service Excellence in Salesforce
